#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rall78 Data-driven sequencer #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
In this example, the limits for the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Sequencer #!EF are 
set automatically according to the number of elements in the x-dimension 
of the data set (as determined by the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Inquire #!EF 
module). #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Open 
(but do not execute) visual program .../DataDrivenSequencer.net. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. 
Select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Sequencer #!EF from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF pull-down menu. 
Note that both the Loop and Palindrome buttons in the control 
panel are already activated (recessed). #!N #!I30 #!N 3. Click on 
the Forward button (>): the visual program executes. The Image window 
opens and the image begins to run continuously through an "animation" 
sequence of two dozen frames. #!N #!I30 #!N 4. Stop the 
animation sequence by: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 
o Clicking on the Stop (&sqbul.) or Pause (  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   || 
#!EF ) button,  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   or #!EF #!N #!I30 #!N o Clicking 
on the Loop and Palindrome buttons to deactivate them. #!N #!I0 
#!N #!EF #!N #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N See 
Sequencer in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference. #!N #!N #!N 
